                <salute><unclear reason="deletion" cert="low" resp="#al">Walt Whitman</unclear>&#8212;Dear Friend<unclear reason="deletion" cert="low" resp="#al">!</unclear> </salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I begin <unclear reason="deletion" cert="high" resp="#ej">this letter</unclear> at <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">11</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> A. M. <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">Sunday</unclear> July <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>&#8212;sitting in the extra<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>l,  <!-- or "d," [#ej]? -->airy hall <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#ej">an apo</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>itting room common to the <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ed log buildings which form so <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">common</unclear> a style of residences of the <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">moderately</unclear> "well off" Southerners&#8212;especially of my section, where saw-mills have not been so plentiful as to favor the building frame houses, and <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">most</unclear> efforts in <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">bried</unclear>-burning have succeeded badly&#8212;producing a very sorry <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#ej">article</unclear>. (I have not determined, before sitting down, when I will finish this and send it on.) The sun is shining bright. This <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">is a tolerably flat</unclear> level place&#8212;convenient for getting about. I <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>out eastward through an orchard of low top<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> Apple and <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> trees. Three hundred yards from <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> house, runs north eastwardly and south westwardly, <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>, or line of more or less closely joined knobs, hills, or short <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">transverse</unclear> ridges about 150 feet high. The ridge runs parallel with the big river and <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ally divides our valley into a sandstone <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">sub</unclear> valley nex<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> broad but low Sand mountain; and a <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>b-vall<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="deletion" cert="low" resp="#al">lime land</unclear> next the ri<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>. Looking <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>h <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>st<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>a <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> new <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>r app<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ching<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>tly stopped <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>erge<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>d a<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">r growth</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">owing</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ickon<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/><hi rend="underline">ggestion</hi> of the <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">present of</unclear> the great <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>s 14 <!-- I'm not sure this last is from the same handwriting --><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">mts.</unclear> whose <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> grandeur would <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> seriously <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">passed</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> mile long isl<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ing lo<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>bil<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">except</unclear> tillers <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> p<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ts; <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">diving th</unclear><gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> and gives only about <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ts vol<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> to<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> share. So, while our ho<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>is <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ch if at all <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">injured</unclear> by <hi rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">malaria</unclear></hi>
            
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01845.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
                
                nd <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>y convenient, and is as I call it <unclear reason="deletion" cert="low" resp="#al">a</unclear> mig<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="deletion" cert="high" resp="#ej">handy</unclear> to <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">bread</unclear> and meat "we yet have not dire<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> from the house any very <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>vely outlook But a <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>inutes travel brings us to <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">parts</unclear> even in the level from which the prospects have a quiet or gent<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> loveliness. A mountain range north of the river coming right in front of me for two or three miles close to the river and giving back a little right and left presents with its top and side green or blue according to season) a pleasing boundary to the landscape.  In the other sub-valley (my <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">term</unclear>) the big, broad mountain and gentle undulations of the valley itself present varying pleasing or soothing scenes. Yet you know mountains whose bigg<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ast might be an elevation of only <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> feet <choice><sic>cant</sic><corr>can't</corr></choice> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>a striking or awe-inspiring appearance to <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">any</unclear> landscape. Most people here live in log houses&#8212;<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>a very few years back, we have partly used <hi rend="underline">wooden and earthen chimneys</hi>, as good stone (that we knew to be such) was not very plentiful about the <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#ej">surface</unclear>, and nobody <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">undertook to <hi rend="underline">mine</hi></unclear> for<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>t and then <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">use</unclear> several f<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>on <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">brickmaking</unclear>, Later <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#al">though has been trying</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/><hi rend="underline">wn sandstone</hi> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>then out <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">stone</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> an<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>eely <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al"><hi rend="underline">dress</hi></unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> a<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> put up. So you<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>he <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><hi rend="underline">e</hi> of <hi rend="underline">q</hi><gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <hi>man</hi> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> with no <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> but a <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">small</unclear><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> (zealous) <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">affords</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> s<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>es of the <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>dge <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>h <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>milk, <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ait, <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">not</unclear> <hi rend="underline">point <!-- or "poem"[#ej]? --></hi> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> away, (a<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>w<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>, many, <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ays, and <hi rend="underline">how mu<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>bor</hi> b<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> u<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ed). Indeed, <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">I love</unclear> to <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> about a <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> in <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> for no
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01845.003.jpg" type="recto"/>
                purpose <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>k up <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ine knots <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>et them <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> is to a wagon wh<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> breathe the<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>, how deli<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>. This valley of two <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>valleys is <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> 10 mi<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> long <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>iles wide&#8212;contains <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>haps 150 grown men The <hi rend="underline">N<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>es</hi> are mostly in t<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/><hi rend="underline">lusters</hi> about two or three <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">miles northeast</unclear> and southwest of my <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">home</unclear>&#8212;they <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>et and well behaved&#8212;perhaps the grown males of the negroes <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> would <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">want</unclear> 30 or 40. Our people are very plain or Democratic <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">in</unclear> ways&#8212;no aristocracy&#8212;little crime&#8212;the religious part are old orthodox Baptists and Methodists. Most of our better educated people are inclined to skpeticism, but don't dispute much with the other class so far as I know. (All the above I have written because your letter of <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">July</unclear> 13 seems <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> for such sketches. <hi rend="underline">I <choice><sic>cant</sic><corr>can't</corr></choice> get a good pen point</hi>. It would take something like a book to deal with all the subjects you open for me.)</p>
            <p>I had one only brother two years older&#8212;in a former letter I said when he was a boy or very young man he was "rude and repellent"&#8212;that only meant his <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ly fault was a <hi rend="underline">teasing <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">&amp;</unclear> jeering</hi> provok<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> way that made me fear often <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>hat h<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>affection was steady and unreliable. He <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> of s<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ness 12 <!-- or "18"[ej]? --><unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#ej">years</unclear>ago&#8212;Major in the Confer<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> Army. He lived and <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> the old homestead 10 South <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>nd his family <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> good <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>minstances<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> me <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> them very much. <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> He <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <!-- is it "and died"[ej]? --> died <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>f a family <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">from Virginia</unclear>&#8212;her m<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>&#8212;<unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">then</unclear> were <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> old families on both <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> but <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> father "raced <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>imself poor&#8212;<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> of <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> was a Mor<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>d, an <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>old-time <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> of N<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>hina
                
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01845.004.jpg" type="verso"/>
                
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">My used</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> was raised <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>mauko<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>out <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>in miles from Baltimore/Ma<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>&#8212;his father <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> is g<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> poor man describ<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>ne by an <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>cquaintance last year <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">ng</unclear> in his old age&#8212;near I<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>as <unclear reason="deletion" resp="#al" cert="low"><choice><orig>tho</orig><reg>though</reg></choice></unclear> not religious yet <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ly one of the most perfect me<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>hat ever lived&#8212;a great  <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ter&#8212;a man of large frame and immense strength&#8212;<unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">is</unclear> remarka<unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">able</unclear> pugilist in his young days&#8212;they moved to upper East Tennessee&#8212;"papa" got a little education&#8212;<unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">went</unclear> to building flat and "keel" boats, and <hi rend="underline">traded</hi> to Nashville and New Orleans, and dealt as a settled merchant at various points <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">east</unclear> Tennessee and North Alabama&#8212;made a <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">small little</unclear> fortune for those times, yet <hi rend="underline">paradoxically</hi> was considered <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">rarely</unclear> honest, candid, liberal&#8212;a man of immense <hi rend="underline">vim<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/></hi> settled <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>gh upon a mountain side with a most magnificent proud outlook&#8212;adorned his home with buildings, and orchards of fruit trees and plants (they came quick into bearing in that day of rich <unclear reason="deletion" cert="low" resp="#al">fresh</unclear> soil). His home was somewhat isolated&#8212;probably he lived among his slaves and a few "retainers" of whit<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> much like a Scottish Chieftain&#8212;yet <unclear reason="illegible">he</unclear> was not <unclear reason="deletion" resp="#al" cert="low">righteous</unclear> nor a <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">conformist</unclear> <choice><orig>tho</orig><reg>though</reg></choice> transmitting <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">to his heirs</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">his</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>t goo<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>s, generosity, and <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>time,)</p>
            
                <p><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">Little Walt is perhaps</unclear> "small" <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">only</unclear> a<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>lacks the <hi rend="underline">draw</hi><gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">ous flesh has</unclear><gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>gh&#8212;started out<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <hi rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">reformer</unclear></hi> rather <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>&#8212;week ac<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> he <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">commenced</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> moved himself into a <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#al" cert="low">room</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> a <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">jug of</unclear> whiskey w<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>hich I was <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al"><hi rend="underline">only</hi> treating</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> neigh<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">workmen at <hi rend="underline">threshing time</hi>. I shall</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <hi rend="underline">slap</hi> him <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">before</unclear> <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/>k got<gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/></p>
            <closer>
                <signed>J.N.J.</signed>
            </closer>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="loc.01845.005.jpg" type="recto"/>
                
                <note type="authorial" place="bottom" anchored="true">Blessed are old <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">bachelors</unclear>.</note>
                <postscript>
                    <ab part="N">Postscript&#8212;Page 1</ab>
                    <p>Did you ever have to <hi rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">pay</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/> postage</hi> because of a foolscap sheet being too <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/>maybe it is.</p>
                    <p>Monday morning <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">could</unclear> get some rain for the wheat <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>her crops&#8212;</p>
                    <p>The largest <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>nt from <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> the <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">small</unclear><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> means. I am glad you <hi rend="underline">could</hi> not<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">slowly</unclear> I came to understand your writi<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>hole&#8212;knowing it myself, I am not <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <hi rend="underline">so vain</hi> a <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">person</unclear> as you might <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">suppose&#8212;at</unclear> first I saw <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">the</unclear> beauty and goodness <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">of</unclear><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> but not the <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>auty and goodness of <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">the whole</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> it seemed <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej">like</unclear> there <hi rend="underline">must</hi> be <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#ej"><hi rend="underline">unnecessary</hi> matter</unclear>&#8212;I see now y<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> finds each item of the Universe an <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><hi rend="underline">part <!-- or "art" [ej]? --></hi>. Was not the fact almost clearly sta<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>Burroughs? <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">â</unclear> Great is (not hard, fatiguing study but)the long persistent <hi rend="underline">scanning</hi> which indescribable, impalpable beauty <hi rend="underline">commands</hi>.</p>
                    <p>In that "Post" paper you sent me, I saw you contemplated a possible both writing and speaking for America <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ter. <hi rend="underline">"I second the motion"</hi>. Suppose you <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al"><hi rend="underline">"lecture"</hi></unclear>! You will draw audiences&#8212;you can <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> that <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#al">disposition</unclear> to <hi rend="underline">give away</hi> all<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>&#8212;you can <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> travel, see more of the <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><hi rend="underline">me</hi> and <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> baby, "publish" <hi rend="underline">yourself</hi><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>ur beliefs) through your own personal<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>uldn't <hi rend="underline">I</hi> like to introduce you to a <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> audience <gap reason="deletion" extent="unk"/> in a more Judicious and <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> than you 
                        
            <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="loc.01845.006.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
                    or any one else would look for? But go ahead and do as you think best.
                    </p>
                    <note type="authorial" place="bottom" anchored="true">Maybe I ought not to send these but they <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> not <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/></note>
                    <ab part="N">Postscript&#8212;Page two</ab>
                    
